# Frontend base components

All form controls and interactive elements in `apps/frontend` must use the project's base components under `@/components/base/*`. These wrap HeroUI primitives and apply the storefront design tokens (`foreground`, `muted`, `input-bg`, etc.) for visual + RTL consistency.

## Required imports

```tsx
import { Button } from "@/components/base/button";
import { Checkbox } from "@/components/base/checkbox";
import { Input } from "@/components/base/input";
import { Select } from "@/components/base/select";
import { Modal } from "@/components/base/modal";
```

## Forbidden in app / section / page code

```tsx
// Native HTML form/interactive tags
<button>…</button>
<input … />
<select>…</select>
<textarea … />

// Direct HeroUI imports
import { Button, Input, Checkbox, Select } from "@heroui/react";
```

## Correct usage

```tsx
<Button variant="primary" fullWidth onPress={onSubmit}>Save</Button>

<Input type="search" value={q} onChange={(e) => setQ(e.target.value)} />

<Checkbox isSelected={checked} onChange={setChecked}>Label</Checkbox>

<Select
  options={[{ id: 'rating', label: 'Top rated' }]}
  selectedKey={sort}
  onSelectionChange={setSort}
/>
```

## Missing a control?

If you need something not yet in `@/components/base/*` (radio, switch, etc.), add a new base proxy file that wraps the HeroUI primitive with project tokens — match the pattern in `button.tsx` / `input.tsx` / `checkbox.tsx` / `select.tsx`. Do not reach for the raw HTML element or import HeroUI directly in app code.

## Exception

The only place allowed to render the raw HeroUI / HTML primitives is the base proxy files themselves (`apps/frontend/src/components/base/*.tsx`).
